Subject:[child_lit] middle school novels about hunger and emotional hunger
Books dealing with emotional hunger stemming from death or an absence of a parent/grandparent:

Sun and Spoon.  Kevin Henkes.
Missing May.  Cynthia Rylant
Love Ruby Lavender.  Deborah Wiles.
Because of Winn Dixie.  Kate DiCamillo.
Becoming Naomi Leone.  Pam Munoz Ryan.
Walk Two Moons.  Sharon Creech.


There's death/absence in these, too, but they also have a particular emphasis on cultural/socioeconomic issues:
Esperanza Rising.  Pam Munoz Ryan.
The Warriors.  Joseph Bruchac
Dave at Night.  Gail Carson Levine.
Bud Not Buddy.  Christopher Paul Curtis.

Irene Fahrenwald
The University of Chicago Laboratory Schools
